        "id": 601
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-04T08:46:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Rummaging about git it looks like 1s comes from 9225dee9655ce607130f9bab5472441b72e25858. It\u0027s the \"if you are writing your first \u0027hello world\u0027 test then this will work reasonably well for you\" type of default. Unless a system is under load (or severely lacking in performance), I don\u0027t see VPP needing more than 1s to generate, traverse graph and capture a (bunch of) frame(s) of packets.\n\nIf you are writing a complicated test, then setting a correct timeout value is exposed, so that you can pass a correct parameter.\n\nThis method (send_and_expect_multi) has been in use since the original submission of this MR (in tests with the common case being \"send a bunch of packets\" on every worker) and it worked fine.\n\nI can\u0027t imagine how a proof that this change, which introduces a tool to be used by others will not break CI when used by others. How would writing an arbitrary test prove that?",
      "parentUuid": "fc5eaa69_1402ef26",
      "revId": "17ab012a809206a32efdc293271b1964e212065c",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
