      "writtenOn": "2026-04-03T17:52:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m glad to see this pulled out of the multi-context test pattern here, but maybe it could have a parameter to opt-in to testing a list of pg interfaces for nothing captured.\n\nThe default timeout should not be hard-coded in multiple places. It would also be really nice to have a smaller default window.  Do you know how 1 sec was chosen?\n\nThe assert_nothing_captured() paradigm is a problematic IMHO as it by construction it must wait an arbitrarily long time to ensure that undesired packets don\u0027t arrive after the timeout.  In this implementation, it there is also the additional non-deterministic delay of the pcap file becoming visible in the file system.  I would think that using pg interface counters could be used to avoid the file system delay, but that relies on the correctness of the stats implementation so may not be a better choice -- \u003csigh\u003e.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 613,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 619,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "17ab012a809206a32efdc293271b1964e212065c",
